						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarmaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kulaśēkharadēva (I)?: Year 5 = 1272-73 A.D. (?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete and damaged.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a gift for a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp and food offerings to the goddess in a temple of a place (name not preserved) by a certain Varandaruvāṉ Paḍāraṉ Kāḍu . ., of Pāttivaśēkaranallūr in Poḻyūr-nāḍu. Other details are lost.</p>						

